
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="normalize.css">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="basic.css">

  <title>08 - more animating masks </title>
</head>
<body>
here I animate a mask over an image background.
<svg id="alice" class="mySvg">
  <defs>
    <mask id="myMask">
      <circle  id="animatedCircleMask" fill="#777" stroke="#fff" stroke-width="5" cy="500" cx="50" r="40"></circle>

      <!-- <image x="50" y="50" xlink:href="texture.jpg"> -->
    </mask>
  </defs>

  <image  mask="url(#myMask)" xlink:href="colours.jpg">
</svg>
<p class="myPara">

  next I will animate a mask over an svg background.
</p>
<svg  class="mySvg">
  <defs>
    <mask id="someMask">

      <image  id="animatedImage" xlink:href="colours.jpg">

      <!-- <image x="50" y="50" xlink:href="texture.jpg"> -->
    </mask>
  </defs>
  <circle  mask="url(#someMask)" fill="#777" stroke="#fff" stroke-width="5" cy="500" cx="300" r="40"></circle>

</svg>
<svg  id="svg-image-blur">
    <image x="10" y="10" id="svg-image" width="300" height="200" xlink:href="http://css-plus.com/examples/2012/03/gaussian-blur/i/fence.jpg" />

    <filter id="blur-effect">
        <feGaussianBlur stdDeviation="1" />
    </filter>
</svg>
<img  src="http://css-plus.com/examples/2012/03/gaussian-blur/i/fence.jpg" alt="">
<script src="index.js" charset="utf-8"></script>
</body>
</html>
